WEBVTT

00:00.201 --> 00:03.335
I'VE SEEN SMALLPOX
SCARES, SARS PANIC,

00:03.337 --> 00:05.504
BUT I'VE NEVER SEEN
ANYTHING LIKE
THIS VIRUS BEFORE.

00:05.506 --> 00:07.106
THE AGENT HAS
BEEN IDENTIFIED

00:07.108 --> 00:08.107
AS AN AVIAN
INFLUENZA THAT

00:08.109 --> 00:09.441
UNTIL NOW HAS
NOT BEEN KNOWN

00:09.443 --> 00:10.442
TO BE
TRANSMITTED

00:10.444 --> 00:11.443
BETWEEN HUMANS.

00:11.445 --> 00:13.379
CLEAR!
[CROWD GASPS]

00:13.381 --> 00:14.847
LOMMERS: SHIPPING
CONTAINERS WERE PLACED

00:14.849 --> 00:16.181
AROUND THE PERIMETER

00:16.183 --> 00:17.549
TO SECURE THE BORDER.

00:17.551 --> 00:18.550
IT'S BAD, BABY.

00:18.552 --> 00:19.852
BUT YOUR OFFICE IS
PROBABLY

00:19.854 --> 00:21.353
THE SAFEST PLACE THAT
YOU CAN BE RIGHT NOW.

00:21.355 --> 00:23.155
STORE'S CLOSED,
EVERYBODY.

00:23.157 --> 00:24.590
WAIT. WAIT. YOU CAN'T JUST--

00:24.592 --> 00:25.924
XANDER:
WHAT THE HELL WAS THAT?

00:25.926 --> 00:27.359
I'M NOT LETTING YOU
GO THROUGH THIS ALONE.

00:27.361 --> 00:28.627
KATIE: OUTSIDE THE WALLS
OF THIS HOSPITAL,

00:28.629 --> 00:30.162
AND WHO'S IN CHARGE?

00:30.164 --> 00:31.330
LOOKS LIKE I AM.

00:31.332 --> 00:32.798
I THINK YOU SHOULD STAY
IN QUARANTINE.

00:32.800 --> 00:34.166
YOU HAVE BEEN EXPOSED.
YOU'VE BEEN OUTSIDE.

00:34.168 --> 00:35.534
BECAUSE WE WENT
TO GET YOU FOOD.

00:35.536 --> 00:36.735
I'M SORRY.

00:36.737 --> 00:38.670
LEO GREENE,
INTHEPERIMETER.COM.

00:38.672 --> 00:40.172
THE FACT THAT
LOMMERS IS TRYING

00:40.174 --> 00:41.774
TO SHUT YOU DOWN
MEANS YOU'RE DOING
SOMETHING RIGHT.

00:41.776 --> 00:43.709
LEO GREENE JUST TOLD
THE WHOLE DAMN WORLD

00:43.711 --> 00:45.544
THERE'S A WAY TO ESCAPE
THE CORDON.

00:45.546 --> 00:47.112
TH--THIS IS THE HOTTEST
STORY IN THE WO--

00:47.114 --> 00:48.647
[COUGHING]

00:48.649 --> 00:50.382
I DON'T WANT TO SPEND
ANOTHER NIGHT AWAY FROM YOU.

00:50.384 --> 00:52.851
ME EITHER.
[SIGNAL FAILS]

00:52.853 --> 00:54.186
[TAPPING KEYS]

00:54.188 --> 00:55.721
I JUST LOST MY
INTERNET CONNECTION.

00:55.723 --> 00:57.356
SO DID EVERYONE
IN THE CORDON.

00:57.358 --> 00:58.590
I ASKED YOU TO STOP
LEO GREENE,

00:58.592 --> 00:59.758
AND YOU DIDN'T.

00:59.760 --> 01:00.793
SO IF YOU'RE LOOKING
FOR SOMEONE

01:00.795 --> 01:02.895
TO BLAME,
BLAME YOURSELF.

01:05.866 --> 01:08.067
[STATIC]

01:14.341 --> 01:16.842
[SIREN IN DISTANCE]

01:16.844 --> 01:18.677
LEX, VOICE-OVER:
OUR GREATEST THREAT

01:18.679 --> 01:21.580
IN A TIME OF CRISIS
IS PANIC.

01:21.582 --> 01:23.515
UNFORTUNATELY, CELL PHONES
AND SOCIAL MEDIA

01:23.517 --> 01:26.285
CAN SPREAD PANIC LIKE
FUEL ON A FIRE,

01:26.287 --> 01:28.954
INCITING UNREST

01:28.956 --> 01:32.291
AND ENCOURAGING ACTIONS THAT
PUT THE PUBLIC AT RISK.

01:32.293 --> 01:34.893
THESE ACTIONS
AFFECT ALL OF US

01:34.895 --> 01:37.763
AND COMPOSE A GREATER THREAT
THAN THE HORRIBLE VIRUS

01:37.765 --> 01:39.064
WE FACE.

01:41.702 --> 01:44.103
IN THE INTEREST
OF PUBLIC SAFETY,

01:44.105 --> 01:46.572
PRECAUTIONARY MEASURES
HAVE BEEN TAKEN TO REMOVE

01:46.574 --> 01:48.574
THIS THREAT FROM WITHIN
THE QUARANTINED SECTION

01:48.576 --> 01:50.709
OF OUR CITY.

01:50.711 --> 01:52.544
THOSE THINGS
GIVE ME THE CREEPS.

01:52.546 --> 01:54.012
LEX, VOICE-OVER:
AND, FORTUNATELY,

01:54.014 --> 01:55.481
JUST 36 HOURS AFTER
ALL COMMUNICATION

01:55.483 --> 01:57.950
WITHIN THE CORDON
WAS SHUT DOWN,

01:57.952 --> 01:59.051
PANIC HAS SUBSIDED.

01:59.053 --> 02:01.987
AND EVERYONE INSIDE
THE CORDON IS SAFER BE...

02:01.989 --> 02:03.255
DENNIS: YOUR BOYFRIEND
SHOULD RUN FOR MAYOR.

02:03.257 --> 02:04.723
TONY:
HE IS PRETTY.

02:04.725 --> 02:06.091
CAREFUL, OR I MIGHT
FORGET TO LET YOU

02:06.093 --> 02:07.392
OUT OF THERE TODAY.

02:07.394 --> 02:08.794
THE NUMBER OF INFECTED
IS DROPPING

02:08.796 --> 02:11.029
AND THE VIRUS
IS UNDER CONTROL.

02:11.031 --> 02:13.532
SOMETHING DOESN'T
FEEL RIGHT.

02:13.534 --> 02:14.867
THEY'RE CALLED HUNGER PAINS.

02:14.869 --> 02:16.401
IGNORE THEM.

02:16.403 --> 02:17.903
THINK HOW SKINNY WE'LL BE.

02:17.905 --> 02:19.338
LEX ON TV: ...THESE RULES
LAID OUT BY THE CDC.

02:19.340 --> 02:20.506
THIS STATION WILL RUN
CONTINUOUSLY

02:20.508 --> 02:22.641
FOR THOSE RESIDENTS
WITHIN THE CORDON.

02:22.643 --> 02:25.144
KEEP IT ON. STAY INDOORS.

02:25.146 --> 02:27.713
AND THIS WILL BE OVER SOON.

02:27.715 --> 02:29.181
WHAT'S WRONG?

02:29.183 --> 02:30.349
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

02:30.351 --> 02:31.617
THE INFECTION RATE
IS DROPPING?

02:31.619 --> 02:33.252
IT'LL BE OVER SOON?

02:33.254 --> 02:34.653
I KNOW HIM, SUZE.

02:34.655 --> 02:37.256
HE HASN'T LIED LIKE
THAT SINCE MY 30TH.

02:37.258 --> 02:39.391
YOUR "SURPRISE" PARTY?

02:39.393 --> 02:41.493
HE DID HIS BEST,
GOD BLESS HIM.

02:41.495 --> 02:43.228
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

02:43.230 --> 02:44.863
I NEED TO TALK TO HIM.

02:44.865 --> 02:48.233
WE NEED THE TRUTH, NOT
A GOVERNMENT SCRIPT.

02:49.837 --> 02:51.503
I'LL BE IN A CLEAN ROOM.

02:51.505 --> 02:52.671
I'M GONNA BUILD

02:52.673 --> 02:53.705
A PHONE
WITH THE POWER TO CALL

02:53.707 --> 02:56.608
OUTSIDE THE DEAD ZONE.

02:56.610 --> 02:59.278
YOU CAN DO THAT?

02:59.280 --> 03:00.812
WE'LL FIND OUT.

03:02.283 --> 03:03.982
[DOOR OPENS]

03:05.953 --> 03:08.453
I GOT TO TALK
TO LOMMERS.

03:08.455 --> 03:10.455
I DIDN'T FEEL
GOOD ABOUT THAT.

03:10.457 --> 03:12.057
WELL, SHE'S IN WASHINGTON.

03:12.059 --> 03:13.225
BE BACK TOMORROW.

03:13.227 --> 03:14.726
BUT RELAX. YOU DID GREAT.

03:14.728 --> 03:16.328
FELLAS,
GIVE US A MINUTE.

03:16.330 --> 03:17.696
ALL RIGHT.

03:19.066 --> 03:21.300
LOOK, THE IMPORTANT THING
IS TO KEEP EVERYONE

03:21.302 --> 03:22.601
IN THERE CALM.

03:22.603 --> 03:23.902
KEEP EVERYONE CALM?

03:23.904 --> 03:25.537
IF YOU WANT TO KEEP
EVERYONE CALM,

03:25.539 --> 03:27.072
LET THEM TALK TO
THEIR FAMILIES.

03:27.074 --> 03:29.174
WE DREW A LINE
THROUGH THE CITY,

03:29.176 --> 03:30.342
TORE FAMILIES APART:

03:30.344 --> 03:31.510
MOTHERS
FROM CHILDREN,

03:31.512 --> 03:32.911
HUSBANDS FROM WIVES.

03:32.913 --> 03:34.680
GIRLFRIENDS FROM BOYFRIENDS.

03:34.682 --> 03:36.515
YOU'RE SAYING THIS
IS PERSONAL.

03:36.517 --> 03:37.983
FINE. IT IS.

03:37.985 --> 03:40.652
BUT IT'S NOT JUST
BECAUSE OF JANA.

03:40.654 --> 03:42.387
THOSE ARE ALL OUR
PEOPLE IN THERE.

03:42.389 --> 03:43.822
AND THEY ARE SAFER NOW.
YOU'VE SEEN THE FOOTAGE.

03:43.824 --> 03:45.224
THE STREETS ARE QUIET.

03:45.226 --> 03:46.658
SO NO ONE'S RIOTING.

03:46.660 --> 03:48.660
BUT DO WE REALLY KNOW
WHAT'S GOING ON?

03:48.662 --> 03:50.662
DO THEY
HAVE ENOUGH FOOD?

03:50.664 --> 03:52.331
DO DIABETICS HAVE
INSULIN?

03:52.333 --> 03:53.732
I GOT MEN WORKING
TRIPLE SHIFTS

03:53.734 --> 03:55.234
GUARDING THAT
PERIMETER,

03:55.236 --> 03:56.401
MEN WITH FAMILIES
INSIDE,

03:56.403 --> 03:57.469
AND THEY HAVE
NO IDEA

03:57.471 --> 03:58.971
WHAT'S GOING
ON IN THERE.

03:58.973 --> 04:00.305
GIVE THEM AN HOUR
A DAY TO TALK

04:00.307 --> 04:01.707
TO THEIR LOVED ONES.

04:01.709 --> 04:03.008
THAT'S NOT
GONNA HAPPEN, LEX.

04:03.010 --> 04:04.376
THESE ARE THE FEDS
WE'RE TALKING ABOUT.

04:04.378 --> 04:05.744
YOU DON'T REASON WITH THEM.

04:05.746 --> 04:06.912
YOU JUST DO
WHAT YOU'RE TOLD.

04:06.914 --> 04:08.747
I GET THAT THIS
IS HARD FOR YOU.

04:08.749 --> 04:10.249
BUT WE'VE GOT A JOB TO DO,
A CITY TO PROTECT.

04:10.251 --> 04:12.651
DON'T SCREW IT UP BY
GETTING EMOTIONAL.

04:14.388 --> 04:18.490
[SIREN IN DISTANCE]

04:18.492 --> 04:20.726
[INDISTINCT PA ANNOUNCEMENTS]

04:29.770 --> 04:31.536
[DOOR HITS HEAVY OBJECT]

04:31.538 --> 04:33.238
[DOOR HITS OBJECT
AGAIN]

04:33.240 --> 04:35.741
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

04:38.846 --> 04:41.046
MAN:
CLOSE IT UP...

04:49.089 --> 04:51.023
CANNERTS: I MUST
DECLARE THE VIRUS AS

04:51.025 --> 04:53.358
HIGHLY CONTAGIOUS
AND FATAL

04:53.360 --> 04:55.560
IN 100% OF ITS VICTIMS.

04:55.562 --> 04:57.029
LOMMERS: I RECOMMEND
WE INSTITUTE

04:57.031 --> 04:58.397
A CORDON SANITAIRE
TO CONTAIN

04:58.399 --> 04:59.464
THE SPREAD OF THE VIRUS.

04:59.466 --> 05:00.999
LEX: WHAT I NEED
IS THE TRUTH...

05:01.001 --> 05:02.501
JAKE: YEAH, I'M IN THE MIDDLE
OF THE DAMN HOT ZONE, LEX.

05:02.503 --> 05:03.502
JANA!

05:03.504 --> 05:04.936
LEX: IF WE LET ANYONE OUT,

05:04.938 --> 05:06.938
WE'RE RISKING THE LIVES
OF EVERYONE IN THIS CITY.

05:12.680 --> 05:14.746
[COUGHING, LABORED BREATHING]

05:17.418 --> 05:18.583
SORRY.

05:18.585 --> 05:20.152
YOU OK?

05:20.154 --> 05:22.754
THE LOBBY. HAVE YOU SEEN
THE BODIES IN THERE?

05:22.756 --> 05:25.157
I HAVE, UNFORTUNATELY.

05:25.159 --> 05:26.358
WE'VE CONVERTED
THE LOBBY TO PROCESS

05:26.360 --> 05:27.926
INCOMING VICTIMS.

05:27.928 --> 05:29.861
THE HOSPITAL IS NOW
DEDICATED EXCLUSIVELY

05:29.863 --> 05:31.029
TO COMBATING THE VIRUS.

05:31.031 --> 05:33.765
AND I'M SORRY YOU HAD
TO SEE THAT.

05:33.767 --> 05:35.801
WALK WITH ME?

05:37.338 --> 05:38.337
KATIE: THERE WERE

05:38.339 --> 05:39.504
SO MANY.

05:39.506 --> 05:40.672
I KNOW.

05:40.674 --> 05:42.040
WE'RE TRYING TO KEEP
IT DISCREET.

05:42.042 --> 05:43.675
NO POINT
IN SPREADING PANIC.

05:43.677 --> 05:45.510
WHAT TOOK YOU UP THERE?

05:45.512 --> 05:48.113
I--I WAS LOOKING FOR
A PHARMACY.

05:48.115 --> 05:49.881
SOMETHING I CAN
HELP YOU WITH?

05:49.883 --> 05:51.983
I NEEDED A PRESCRIPTION.

05:51.985 --> 05:55.320
TEXTING IT IN ISN'T
REALLY AN OPTION. SO...

05:55.322 --> 05:56.655
ZENQUELL. IT'S, UM...

05:56.657 --> 05:57.989
I'M FAMILIAR WITH IT.

05:57.991 --> 06:00.225
HOW LONG HAVE YOU
BEEN DIAGNOSED?

06:01.962 --> 06:03.161
IT'S NOT IMPORTANT.

06:03.163 --> 06:05.230
I'LL HAVE A LOOK,
SEE WHAT WE HAVE.

06:05.232 --> 06:06.398
THANK YOU.

06:06.400 --> 06:07.999
THIS IS ME.

06:08.001 --> 06:09.835
I'M AFRAID THE LOBBY
ISN'T THE ONLY THING

06:09.837 --> 06:11.937
WE'VE BEEN FORCED
TO REPURPOSE.

06:25.652 --> 06:27.652
[MICE SQUEAKING]

06:27.654 --> 06:29.287
JAKE: EVEN ON
A GOOD DAY,

06:29.289 --> 06:30.689
8 MEN ISN'T ENOUGH.

06:30.691 --> 06:32.290
BUT WITH OUR
COMMS DOWN--

06:32.292 --> 06:33.792
COMMUNICATIONS--

06:33.794 --> 06:35.060
WE CAN'T CALL EACH
OTHER,

06:35.062 --> 06:36.661
WHICH MAKES POLICE WORK
TOUGH

06:36.663 --> 06:38.597
'CAUSE YOU GOT
NO BACKUP.

06:38.599 --> 06:40.098
SO HOW DO YOU GUYS TALK?

06:40.100 --> 06:41.299
OH, WE MEET UP
ONCE A DAY,

06:41.301 --> 06:42.300
FILL EACH OTHER IN.

06:42.302 --> 06:43.468
IT'S NOT IDEAL,

06:43.470 --> 06:45.837
BUT WE GOT TO PLAY THE
HAND WE'RE DEALT, RIGHT?

06:45.839 --> 06:47.839
WHY CAN'T THEY SEND IN
MORE COPS?

06:47.841 --> 06:49.307
THAT'S A GOOD QUESTION.

06:49.309 --> 06:51.576
I GUESS THEY DON'T WANT
TO RISK THEM GETTING SICK.

06:51.578 --> 06:53.311
YOU GOT ANYBODY
ON THE OUTSIDE?

06:53.313 --> 06:55.781
YEAH, YEAH. I GOT--
I GOT PEOPLE.

06:55.783 --> 06:58.150
NO, I MEAN, LIKE A GIRL.

06:58.152 --> 06:59.484
[CHUCKLES]

06:59.486 --> 07:01.219
A GIRL?

07:02.589 --> 07:04.289
NO. WHY? DO--DO YOU?

07:04.291 --> 07:05.757
NO.

07:05.759 --> 07:07.893
YEAH, YOU'RE RIGHT.
GIRLS ARE GROSS.

07:07.895 --> 07:10.162
NICE!
WAY TO BE A ROLE MODEL.

07:10.164 --> 07:11.396
AH. HEY.

07:11.398 --> 07:12.397
THIS IS GUY TALK.

07:12.399 --> 07:13.598
YOU'RE NOT SUPPOSED
TO BE LISTENING.

07:13.600 --> 07:14.800
YEAH, MOM. IT'S GUY TALK.

07:14.802 --> 07:16.701
JAKE: YEAH.

07:16.703 --> 07:19.271
WHERE'D YOU GET
THAT HAT?

07:19.273 --> 07:20.639
JAKE: OH, I GRABBED
IT FOR HIM

07:20.641 --> 07:21.973
OUT OF THE OLD
LOST AND FOUND.

07:21.975 --> 07:24.509
LOOKS GOOD, RIGHT?
DID YOU, UH--

07:24.511 --> 07:25.777
DID YOU GET WHAT
YOU NEED?

07:25.779 --> 07:28.113
THE PHARMACY'S SHUT DOWN.

07:28.115 --> 07:30.415
GUESS I'LL HAVE TO LIVE
WITHOUT TOOTHPASTE.

07:30.417 --> 07:31.616
JAKE: YOU SEE?

07:31.618 --> 07:34.019
GIRLS ARE GROSS.

07:35.522 --> 07:37.856
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

07:37.858 --> 07:39.724
I NEED A SIGNAL BOOSTER.

07:39.726 --> 07:41.693
YOU CAN'T, LIKE,
LINK UP OUR PHONES

07:41.695 --> 07:43.094
TO MAKE THEM STRONGER?

07:43.096 --> 07:44.396
NO, IT DOESN'T WORK
THAT WAY.

07:44.398 --> 07:46.565
I NEED A DIRECTIONAL SIGNAL
WITH THE POWER

07:46.567 --> 07:48.533
TO REACH A WORKING
CELL TOWER.

07:48.535 --> 07:51.069
NOT THAT I DON'T THINK
THIS IS AN AWESOME IDEA.

07:51.071 --> 07:52.904
LIKE, IT TOTALLY IS,

07:52.906 --> 07:54.906
BUT WHAT EXACTLY
ARE YOU HOPING LEX

07:54.908 --> 07:56.374
WILL BE ABLE TELL US
IF THIS WORKS?

07:56.376 --> 07:59.544
HOW TO SURVIVE, HOW
MUCH FOOD WE'LL NEED.

07:59.546 --> 08:01.580
IS--ARE WE BETTER OFF IN
HERE OR ON THE MOVE?

08:01.582 --> 08:02.881
OR IS THE WATER SAFE?

08:02.883 --> 08:04.216
HOW QUICKLY IS
THE VIRUS SPREADING?

08:04.218 --> 08:05.884
YOU AND I HAVE BEEN THROUGH
TOUGH TIMES, SUZE.

08:05.886 --> 08:07.552
BUT RIGHT NOW,
WE HAVE NO IDEA

08:07.554 --> 08:08.954
OF WHAT WE'RE UP AGAINST.

08:08.956 --> 08:10.622
TONY: THERE.

08:10.624 --> 08:12.924
THERE IT WAS AGAIN.

08:12.926 --> 08:14.993
[HELICOPTER PASSES]

08:14.995 --> 08:16.294
[TAPPING ON WALL]

08:16.296 --> 08:18.497
THERE'S SOMEONE
IN THE GARAGE.

08:18.499 --> 08:20.866
WHAT ARE THEY DOING?

08:20.868 --> 08:22.434
WE'VE ONLY CAUGHT
GLIMPSES OF THEM.

08:22.436 --> 08:25.036
DENNIS:
HOW'S THE PHONE COMING?

08:25.038 --> 08:27.772
SLOWLY. I NEED TO GET
ON THE ROOF.

08:27.774 --> 08:29.174
YOU'LL GET IT DONE.

08:29.176 --> 08:31.610
NO ONE'S BETTER AT
MICROELECTRONICS THAN YOU.

08:31.612 --> 08:35.080
DENNIS, THAT SOUNDED
CURIOUSLY LIKE A COMPLIMENT.

08:35.082 --> 08:37.382
NAH, I'VE BEEN IN
QUARANTINE FOR 2 DAYS.

08:37.384 --> 08:38.950
I MUST BE DELIRIOUS.

08:38.952 --> 08:40.986
I WAS JUST THINKING, UM,

08:40.988 --> 08:43.622
POOR ISOLATED TONY
AND I SHOULD, UH, GET

08:43.624 --> 08:45.657
TO MAKE THE FIRST
PHONE CALL.

08:45.659 --> 08:48.760
YOU HAVE AN HOUR TO GO.
PUT A LID ON THE PITY PARTY.

08:48.762 --> 08:50.562
[COMPUTER BEEP, DOOR OPENS]

09:13.720 --> 09:15.353
GREENE: QUIET IN HERE.

09:16.456 --> 09:18.423
I GUESS IT TAKES
A LOT OF MEN TO GUARD

09:18.425 --> 09:20.091
A BIG PRISON, HUH?

09:22.162 --> 09:24.963
SO I HAVE SOMETHING
TO ASK YOU.

09:26.166 --> 09:28.066
FIRST YOU SLAP A GAG
ON MY FRIENDS.

09:28.068 --> 09:29.467
NOW YOU WON'T TALK
TO ME.

09:29.469 --> 09:31.636
WHICH FRIENDS? THE ONES
THAT LEAKED THAT STORY

09:31.638 --> 09:33.405
ABOUT WHERE TO BREAK
THROUGH THE BARRICADES?

09:33.407 --> 09:35.807
THAT LITTLE NEWS PIECE
OF YOURS,

09:35.809 --> 09:38.343
THAT'S HALF THE REASON
COMMUNICATION GOT SHUT DOWN.

09:38.345 --> 09:40.345
AND WHAT'S
THE OTHER HALF?

09:40.347 --> 09:42.180
KEEP THE VIRUS
FROM SPREADING

09:42.182 --> 09:44.182
OR HIDE THE SECRETS
INSIDE?

09:44.184 --> 09:45.383
YOU...

09:45.385 --> 09:47.652
YOU'RE RIGHT.

09:47.654 --> 09:49.854
YOU'RE RIGHT.
WE'RE ALL JUST LITTLE PAWNS

09:49.856 --> 09:52.157
IN THIS BIG EVIL PLOT
TO DESTROY ATLANTA.

09:52.159 --> 09:53.325
OR AT LEAST LIE TO IT.

09:53.327 --> 09:54.726
WELL, IT'S SURE LUCKY
FOR LOMMERS

09:54.728 --> 09:56.561
SHE'S FOUND SUCH
AN HONEST FACE

09:56.563 --> 09:58.296
TO DO IT FOR HER.

09:58.298 --> 10:00.865
THAT PICTURE YOU WERE
LOOKING AT OVER THERE,

10:00.867 --> 10:02.367
IS THAT YOUR GIRL?

10:02.369 --> 10:03.868
THAT'S NONE OF
YOUR BUSINESS.

10:03.870 --> 10:05.804
ALL RIGHT. LISTEN,
MY FRIENDS

10:05.806 --> 10:07.672
AND CONTACTS I HAVE
ON THE INSIDE,

10:07.674 --> 10:09.140
I THINK
THEY'RE SICK.

10:09.142 --> 10:10.342
AND--AND I--I NEED
TO KNOW

10:10.344 --> 10:11.710
WHAT'S HAPPENING
TO THEM.

10:15.215 --> 10:17.082
SORRY TO HEAR THAT.

10:17.084 --> 10:19.884
I KNOW HOW YOU FEEL,
BUT MY HANDS ARE TIED.

10:19.886 --> 10:21.886
RIGHT, BECAUSE YOU LET
LOMMERS TIE THEM.

10:21.888 --> 10:23.588
GET OUT.

10:28.562 --> 10:30.228
I DON'T GET WHY
YOU'RE MORE LOYAL

10:30.230 --> 10:32.397
TO SOME WOMAN WITH
A FANCY TITLE

10:32.399 --> 10:34.499
THAN TO SOMEONE YOU
CLAIM TO LOVE.

10:43.877 --> 10:46.244
SINGER: ♪ I'M WIDE-EYED
AND IT'S MIDNIGHT ♪

10:46.246 --> 10:48.913
♪ AND ALL I SEE IS YOU ♪

10:48.915 --> 10:51.549
♪ ALL THE HEADS... ♪

10:51.551 --> 10:54.519
A LITTLE DISTANCE MIGHT
BE GOOD FOR THE TWO OF YOU.

10:54.521 --> 10:56.621
IT'LL HELP YOU SEE
THINGS MORE CLEARLY.

10:56.623 --> 10:59.324
WE SEE THINGS FINE, MA.

10:59.326 --> 11:01.526
WELL, WHEN YOU'RE
DONE REMINISCING,

11:01.528 --> 11:03.161
I COULD USE SOME HELP
IN THE HERE AND NOW.

11:03.163 --> 11:04.796
WE SHOULDN'T EVEN
BE OPEN.

11:04.798 --> 11:06.131
WE JUST HAD REDNECKS
WITH GUNS

11:06.133 --> 11:07.499
HELPING THEMSELVES
TO INVENTORY.

11:07.501 --> 11:08.800
I BUILT THIS STORE.

11:08.802 --> 11:10.869
AND IT'S PAID FOR EVERY
PRIVILEGE YOU'VE EVER HAD.

11:10.871 --> 11:12.937
SO I WON'T BE SCARED
OUT OF IT.

11:12.939 --> 11:16.307
NOW, COME HELP ME
RESTOCK THE SHELVES.

11:16.309 --> 11:17.542
FINE.

11:17.544 --> 11:20.945
BUT WHEN XANDER COMES,
I'M MOVING TO GRANDMA'S.

11:20.947 --> 11:24.282
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
"WHEN XANDER COMES"?

11:24.284 --> 11:25.650
HE SAID HE DOESN'T
WANT ME

11:25.652 --> 11:27.786
GOING THROUGH THIS
ALONE.

11:27.788 --> 11:29.688
HE'S GONNA FIND
HIS WAY IN.

11:29.690 --> 11:31.756
YOU REALLY ARE DELUSIONAL.

11:58.819 --> 12:00.785
[CLANG]

12:00.787 --> 12:04.022
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

12:04.024 --> 12:05.924
YOU SHOULDN'T BE ALONE
UP HERE.

12:05.926 --> 12:08.827
I--I JUST NEED THIS DISH.
I DON'T WANT ANY TROUBLE.

12:08.829 --> 12:10.695
YOU'RE FROM
THE TOP FLOOR.

12:11.898 --> 12:13.264
YEAH.

12:13.266 --> 12:14.999
YEAH, I'M FROM BITSCAN.

12:15.001 --> 12:16.534
WHY ARE YOU UP HERE?

12:18.672 --> 12:20.205
I KNOW YOU.

12:20.207 --> 12:22.207
I'M AROUND A LOT,

12:22.209 --> 12:25.844
EXCEPT FOR YOUR
FLOOR, OF COURSE.

12:25.846 --> 12:27.178
SAM...

12:27.180 --> 12:30.548
HEAD OF BUILDING OPS
AND MAINTENANCE.

12:30.550 --> 12:32.617
JANA.

12:34.621 --> 12:36.287
S--SORRY ABOUT THAT.

12:36.289 --> 12:38.156
[DROPS PIPE]
I THOUGHT YOU WERE

12:38.158 --> 12:39.457
ONE OF THE TWEAKERS
FROM THE GARAGE.

12:39.459 --> 12:41.326
IS THAT WHY YOU'RE
UP HERE?

12:43.363 --> 12:45.463
HIGH GROUND'S THE SAFEST
PLACE IN A STORM, RIGHT,

12:45.465 --> 12:48.900
EXCEPT FOR BITSCAN,
OF COURSE.

12:48.902 --> 12:51.002
YOU GOT ROOM FOR
ONE MORE IN THERE?

12:51.004 --> 12:53.371
WE AGREED NO ONE GETS IN.

12:53.373 --> 12:56.007
I MADE THE RULE. TH--THEY'D
NEVER LET ME BREAK IT.

12:56.009 --> 12:58.777
[SIREN IN DISTANCE]

12:58.779 --> 13:01.780
SORRY.

13:01.782 --> 13:03.681
GET WHAT YOU'RE AFTER

13:03.683 --> 13:05.884
AND GET BACK TO YOUR
SAFE LITTLE FORT.

13:17.230 --> 13:19.097
I'M SORRY I COULDN'T
FIND WHAT YOU NEED.

13:19.099 --> 13:20.865
I CAN LOOK FOR SOMETHING
COMPARABLE,

13:20.867 --> 13:23.067
BUT FINDING THE BALANCE
IN MEDICATIONS LIKE THESE

13:23.069 --> 13:24.769
CAN BE COMPLICATED.

13:24.771 --> 13:26.604
I'M ALL TOO FAMILIAR
WITH THAT DANCE.

13:28.842 --> 13:30.141
JAKE: HEY.

13:30.143 --> 13:32.277
EVERYTHING OK?

13:32.279 --> 13:34.078
YEAH. DR. CANNERTS WAS
LOOKING

13:34.080 --> 13:36.214
FOR SOME ALLERGY MEDICINE
FOR BRITNEY.

13:36.216 --> 13:37.715
I'M AFRAID OUR
PHARMACEUTICAL SUPPLIES

13:37.717 --> 13:38.883
ARE RATHER LOW.

13:38.885 --> 13:40.485
JAKE: HEY. I'M, UH,

13:40.487 --> 13:42.187
I'M HEADING OUT ON PATROL.

13:42.189 --> 13:43.588
HAVE YOU SEEN MY--
MY BLACK T-SHIRT?

13:43.590 --> 13:44.889
THAT ONE?

13:44.891 --> 13:46.958
IT WAS
PRETTY RIPE.

13:50.096 --> 13:51.863
YOU ACTUALLY TOUCHED
THAT THING.

13:51.865 --> 13:54.933
I WORE GLOVES.

13:54.935 --> 13:57.202
[KATIE CHUCKLES]

13:57.204 --> 13:59.037
I'LL TRADE YOU FOR
THAT HEALTH HAZARD

13:59.039 --> 14:00.371
YOU'VE GOT ON.

14:00.373 --> 14:01.606
JAKE: OH, YOU DON'T
WANT TO TOUCH THIS ONE.

14:01.608 --> 14:03.274
IT'S TOXIC.

14:05.912 --> 14:08.947
YOU REALLY THINK YOU'RE
GONNA GET ALL THIS OVERTIME?

14:08.949 --> 14:11.916
HEY. THEY OWE, THEY PAY.

14:13.720 --> 14:15.653
IS THAT WHAT YOUR
BOOKIE LIKES TO SAY?

14:17.958 --> 14:19.657
ANYBODY UP THERE
HUNGRY?

14:19.659 --> 14:21.960
DD'S SMOKEHOUSE,
HOT AND READY.

14:21.962 --> 14:23.261
LOOK AT YOU

14:23.263 --> 14:25.129
SPRINGING FOR
THE GOOD STUFF.

14:25.131 --> 14:26.965
YOU KNOW HOW I DO.

14:29.569 --> 14:30.802
HEY, WALDEN,

14:30.804 --> 14:32.637
ISN'T IT YOUR DAUGHTER'S
BIRTHDAY TODAY?

14:32.639 --> 14:34.005
WALDEN: LORELAI,

14:34.007 --> 14:35.840
EIGHT YEARS OLD TODAY.

14:35.842 --> 14:37.208
WHY DON'T YOU TAKE ONE
OF THESE BAGS

14:37.210 --> 14:38.843
AND GO SHARE IT
WITH YOUR FAMILY?

14:38.845 --> 14:41.246
I'LL TAKE YOUR POST. GO.

14:41.248 --> 14:43.414
AND BE THANKFUL THAT YOU
BOUGHT THAT PLACE

14:43.416 --> 14:44.949
IN KIRKWOOD LAST SPRING.

14:44.951 --> 14:45.984
THANKS, LEX.

14:49.155 --> 14:50.521
[SQUEAKING]

15:04.137 --> 15:05.637
YOU OK?

15:10.310 --> 15:13.878
I SPENT MY LIFE HUNTING
FOR A VIRUS LIKE THIS.

15:13.880 --> 15:15.179
PERFECT.

15:15.181 --> 15:17.382
NOW IT'S DESTROYING US.

15:17.384 --> 15:18.683
IT WON'T RESPOND
TO THE DRUGS I HAVE.

15:18.685 --> 15:20.818
AND THE ONES I NEED
ARE TANGLED

15:20.820 --> 15:22.754
IN A WEB OF BUREAUCRACY
TRYING TO FIND THEIR WAY

15:22.756 --> 15:23.922
TO ME.

15:23.924 --> 15:25.723
NOTHING GETS IN OR OUT.

15:25.725 --> 15:27.692
GOOD PATROL?

15:27.694 --> 15:29.594
FOUND MORE BODIES OVER
AT RENAISSANCE PARK.

15:29.596 --> 15:31.729
IT SEEMS TO BE A POPULAR
PLACE TO DROP THEM.

15:31.731 --> 15:33.197
DID YOU BURN THEM?

15:33.199 --> 15:34.465
GOOD.

15:36.102 --> 15:37.936
HEY, UH...

15:37.938 --> 15:39.537
EARLIER WITH KATIE,

15:39.539 --> 15:41.005
I HEARD YOU SAYING YOU--

15:41.007 --> 15:43.107
YOU COULDN'T FIND
SOMETHING--A MEDICATION?

15:43.109 --> 15:44.409
I DOUBT SHE WOULD
APPRECIATE

15:44.411 --> 15:45.910
MY DISCUSSING IT
WITH YOU.

15:45.912 --> 15:46.978
I--I WASN'T PRYING.

15:46.980 --> 15:48.680
JUST, THERE'S A PHARMACY
ACROSS THE PARK.

15:48.682 --> 15:50.281
IT'S PROBABLY PRETTY LOOTED,
BUT I COULD CHECK IT OUT

15:50.283 --> 15:51.349
ON MY NEXT PATROL.

15:51.351 --> 15:52.583
MAYBE THEY HAVE WHAT
SHE NEEDS.

15:52.585 --> 15:53.751
THAT'S VERY KIND OF YOU.

15:53.753 --> 15:55.320
I COULD USE A FEW
THINGS MYSELF.

15:55.322 --> 15:56.487
YEAH.

15:56.489 --> 15:58.890
I'LL MAKE A LIST.
THANK YOU.

15:59.893 --> 16:02.026
[SIRENS,
POLICE RADIO TRANSMISSIONS]

16:08.768 --> 16:10.068
LEX...

16:10.070 --> 16:11.235
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING OUT HERE?

16:11.237 --> 16:12.537
I MEAN, DON'T THEY
GOT YOU SET UP

16:12.539 --> 16:13.871
IN SOME TV STUDIO,

16:13.873 --> 16:15.606
WITH CUTE GIRLS
BRINGING YOU COFFEE?

16:15.608 --> 16:17.942
IT'S NOT LIKE THAT.

16:17.944 --> 16:19.243
OK...

16:19.245 --> 16:20.945
THAT'S EXACTLY
WHAT IT'S LIKE.

16:20.947 --> 16:22.213
HA HA.
YOU WANT TO TRADE?

16:22.215 --> 16:25.116
WELL, YOU CONVINCE LOMMERS
AND THE GIG'S ALL YOURS.

16:25.118 --> 16:26.250
MM-HMM.

16:26.252 --> 16:27.952
YOU GOT ANYBODY INSIDE?

16:27.954 --> 16:29.253
NAH.

16:29.255 --> 16:30.989
I MEAN,
I KNOW SOME PEOPLE.

16:30.991 --> 16:32.991
BUT IT'S NOT LIKE YOU.

16:41.534 --> 16:44.469
HEY! THIS AREA'S
OFF-LIMITS.

16:44.471 --> 16:46.838
TURN AROUND AND MOVE ON!

16:50.777 --> 16:53.511
LEX: WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.
I KNOW THAT KID.

16:55.782 --> 16:58.516
HEY! THAT FENCE IS
ELECTRIFIED. STOP!

17:00.887 --> 17:02.887
HEY! NO, NO, NO!

17:04.924 --> 17:07.658
HEY! DON'T DO IT, KID.
WE WILL SHOOT!

17:12.632 --> 17:14.699
THIS IS
YOUR FINAL WARNING!

17:30.817 --> 17:35.319
[POLICE RADIO TRANSMISSIONS,
INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

17:35.321 --> 17:36.821
XANDER: THAT COP SHOT ME.

17:36.823 --> 17:38.856
I WAS JUST TRYING TO GET
TO MY GIRL,

17:38.858 --> 17:40.191
AND HE SHOT ME.

17:40.193 --> 17:42.693
WITH A BEANBAG.
QUIT YOUR CRYING.

17:42.695 --> 17:45.463
LEAVE HIM BE.
IT'S NOT HIS FAULT.

17:47.133 --> 17:48.933
THIS CITY'S GOING
TO HELL.

17:55.842 --> 17:59.077
[TAP ON GLASS]

17:59.079 --> 18:00.812
I NEED
TO FINISH THIS.

18:00.814 --> 18:04.182
FINISH IN THE MORNING.
YOU NEED SLEEP.

18:04.184 --> 18:06.651
I'LL BE OK.

18:10.490 --> 18:13.624
HEY. WHERE'S
YOUR BIRTH MOTHER?

18:13.626 --> 18:14.992
DO YOU REMEMBER
THE FIRST TIME

18:14.994 --> 18:16.227
YOU ASKED ME THAT?

18:16.229 --> 18:18.463
YOU WERE 8.

18:18.465 --> 18:20.364
YOU TOLD ME SHE WAS
STUCK IN CUBA.

18:20.366 --> 18:23.501
I SAID, "SHE SENT ME
OVER ON A LIFE RAFT

18:23.503 --> 18:25.203
"BUT GOT CAUGHT
BEFORE SHE COULD

18:25.205 --> 18:26.637
CLIMB IN BEHIND ME."

18:26.639 --> 18:27.805
AND AS SOON AS
SHE COULD ESCAPE,

18:27.807 --> 18:29.307
SHE'D BE COMING FOR YOU.

18:29.309 --> 18:30.908
I ACTUALLY BELIEVED IT.

18:30.910 --> 18:32.877
HMM, SO DID I.

18:35.415 --> 18:36.781
I JUST...

18:37.817 --> 18:39.484
I WANTED SO BAD TO
BELIEVE THAT THERE

18:39.486 --> 18:41.519
WAS SOMEONE OUT
THERE WHO LOVED ME.

18:42.856 --> 18:45.256
AND NOW SOMEONE
ACTUALLY DOES.

18:45.258 --> 18:47.058
OH, NO, JANA.

18:47.060 --> 18:48.926
AND THE ONLY REASON
WHY I'M IN HERE

18:48.928 --> 18:50.528
INSTEAD OF ASLEEP IN
HIS BED IS BECAUSE

18:50.530 --> 18:52.163
I WAS TOO DAMN
AFRAID TO LET MYSELF

18:52.165 --> 18:53.831
BELIEVE IT.

18:56.469 --> 18:57.835
I'M OK.

18:59.239 --> 19:01.239
I JUST NEED
TO FINISH THIS.

19:12.352 --> 19:14.519
WE GOT TO STOP
MEETING LIKE THIS.

19:14.521 --> 19:16.420
YOU GOT A TRACKER ON
ME OR SOMETHING?

19:16.422 --> 19:17.922
IF I SAID "YES,"
WOULD YOU QUIT TRYING

19:17.924 --> 19:20.057
TO BREAK IN TO SEE
YOUR GIRLFRIEND?

19:33.940 --> 19:35.473
I THINK THIS IS THE PART
WHERE YOU APOLOGIZE

19:35.475 --> 19:37.008
FOR SHOOTING ME IN MY BACK.

19:37.010 --> 19:38.276
YOU'RE THE ONE WHO
BROKE THE LAW.

19:38.278 --> 19:39.644
IT'S A BAD LAW.

19:39.646 --> 19:41.012
AND WHAT DO YOU CARE
IF I GET IN?

19:41.014 --> 19:42.079
IT SETS A PRECEDENT.

19:42.081 --> 19:44.048
WHEN PEOPLE STOP BELIEVING
IN THE QUARANTINE,

19:44.050 --> 19:45.616
PEOPLE LIKE YOU
TRYING TO SLIP IN,

19:45.618 --> 19:47.418
SICK PEOPLE TRYING
TO SLIP OUT.

19:47.420 --> 19:50.621
O--OK, THE THING IS,

19:50.623 --> 19:52.557
THE GOVERNMENT SAYS
THIS IS ALMOST OVER.

19:52.559 --> 19:55.159
AND YOU'RE HERE TALKING
ABOUT PRECEDENTS,

19:55.161 --> 19:56.794
LIKE...

19:56.796 --> 19:58.496
LIKE IT'S SOMETHING WE
MIGHT HAVE TO LIVE WITH

19:58.498 --> 20:00.264
FOR A LONG TIME.

20:00.266 --> 20:01.766
WHICH ONE IS IT?

20:01.768 --> 20:03.668
JUST TRYING TO KEEP
EVERYONE SAFE.

20:04.871 --> 20:07.805
MY GIRL TERESA IS
9 MONTHS' PREGNANT.

20:07.807 --> 20:11.442
ARE YOU SAYING SHE'S
SAFE IN THERE WITHOUT ME?

20:11.444 --> 20:13.611
CONGRATULATIONS.

20:13.613 --> 20:15.146
I'M NOT MISSING
THE BIRTH OF MY DAUGHTER.

20:15.148 --> 20:17.615
I'M SORRY THAT YOU
CAN'T BE--

20:17.617 --> 20:18.983
I JUST TOLD YOU.
I WILL BE.

20:18.985 --> 20:20.318
DAMN IT, KID.

20:20.320 --> 20:21.586
"KID"?

20:22.689 --> 20:24.822
NO, THE WAY I SEE IT,

20:24.824 --> 20:27.124
I'M THE ONLY ONE OF US
MAN ENOUGH

20:27.126 --> 20:28.359
TO DO WHAT'S RIGHT.

20:30.230 --> 20:32.997
[INDISTINCT PA ANNOUNCEMENTS]

20:32.999 --> 20:34.298
EXCUSE ME. HI.

20:34.300 --> 20:36.500
I'M LOOKING FOR A
PATIENT ON THIS FLOOR--

20:36.502 --> 20:38.035
XANDER PAULSON.

20:38.037 --> 20:39.237
LEX: NO WAY.

20:39.239 --> 20:41.639
THAT YOUNG MAN HAS BEEN
THROUGH ENOUGH ALREADY.

20:41.641 --> 20:44.041
YOU ARE NOT GONNA USE HIM
TO MAKE HEADLINES.

20:44.043 --> 20:46.344
OH, HE'S NOT THE HEADLINE,
ACTUALLY. YOU ARE.

20:46.346 --> 20:48.145
HERO COP SHOOTS ROMEO
IN BACK.

20:48.147 --> 20:49.747
I JUST WANT TO GET
HIS SIDE OF IT.

20:49.749 --> 20:51.882
YOU DO NOT GO NEAR
THAT KID.

20:51.884 --> 20:53.251
OH, YEAH? WHAT ARE
YOU GONNA DO?

20:53.253 --> 20:54.652
YOU GONNA SHOOT ME, TOO?

20:54.654 --> 20:55.820
OH, AND DEPRIVE MYSELF
THE PLEASURE

20:55.822 --> 20:57.355
OF KICKING YOUR ASS?

20:57.357 --> 20:59.023
HA HA. IS THAT A THREAT?

20:59.025 --> 21:00.725
ARE YOU PHYSICALLY
THREATENING ME?

21:00.727 --> 21:02.860
I AM ORDERING YOU
TO LEAVE THIS HOSPITAL

21:02.862 --> 21:05.162
AND OFFERING TO
PHYSICALLY ASSIST YOU

21:05.164 --> 21:06.964
IF NECESSARY.

21:09.135 --> 21:11.102
YOU'RE GOING TO BE
ON THE WRONG SIDE

21:11.104 --> 21:12.870
OF HISTORY, ALEX.

21:14.173 --> 21:16.073
IS THIS REALLY WHO
YOU WANT TO BE?

21:21.714 --> 21:24.148
[THUNDER]

21:42.902 --> 21:45.002
[RUMBLING INSIDE TRUCK]

21:54.013 --> 21:57.748
ATLANTA PD.
ANYONE IN THERE?

22:32.985 --> 22:33.984
HEY!

22:53.506 --> 22:55.239
[PANTING]

23:08.755 --> 23:10.454
MY POINT IS IT'S EASY
TO SAY,

23:10.456 --> 23:12.456
"DON'T WORRY, GIRL. I'M
GONNA TAKE CARE OF YOU."

23:12.458 --> 23:16.627
WHEN THAT BABY IS CRYING AND
IT'S 2:00 IN THE MORNING,

23:16.629 --> 23:17.962
IT'S ANOTHER STORY.

23:17.964 --> 23:19.430
XANDER IS NOT LIKE THAT.

23:19.432 --> 23:20.631
[LEANNE SCOFFS]

23:20.633 --> 23:23.834
RIGHT! NO. XANDER IS
RESPONSIBLE.

23:23.836 --> 23:25.302
WHY IS THAT SO HARD
TO BELIEVE?

23:25.304 --> 23:28.873
LEANNE: YOU REALLY WANT
ME TO ANSWER THAT?

23:28.875 --> 23:30.040
I WAS THERE, TOO,
YOU KNOW?

23:30.042 --> 23:31.442
THIS ISN'T ALL
ON HIM.

23:31.444 --> 23:33.477
EXACTLY.

23:33.479 --> 23:37.415
NEITHER ONE OF YOU
ARE READY TO BE A PARENT.

23:37.417 --> 23:38.516
[SIGHS]

23:38.518 --> 23:39.917
WHO ARE YOU TO JUDGE?

23:39.919 --> 23:41.318
I CAN'T REMEMBER
THE LAST TIME YOU

23:41.320 --> 23:43.020
AND DAD SAID SOMETHING
NICE TO EACH OTHER.

23:43.022 --> 23:44.588
IS THAT WHAT YOU
WANT FROM ME?

23:44.590 --> 23:45.756
YOU WANT ME TO
END UP LIKE--

23:45.758 --> 23:47.258
[VEHICLE RAPIDLY APPROACHING]

23:49.462 --> 23:50.461
MOM.

23:51.864 --> 23:54.698
GOOD AFTERNOON, LADIES.

23:54.700 --> 23:57.468
WHERE'S YOUR COP FRIEND NOW?

23:57.470 --> 23:58.569
[HARLEY'S FRIENDS CHUCKLING]

23:58.571 --> 23:59.570
HARLEY: GET TO IT, BOYS.

23:59.572 --> 24:00.838
I WANT TO SEE IF WE CAN FIT

24:00.840 --> 24:02.239
EVERYTHING IN HERE IN
THE BACK OF MY TRUCK.

24:18.891 --> 24:21.091
[TAP ON GLASS]

24:23.629 --> 24:24.795
HOW DID IT GO?

24:24.797 --> 24:25.796
I FOUND EVERYTHING,
EXCEPT FOR, UH,

24:25.798 --> 24:28.132
NUCLOVIR AND TRIVINQUILL.

24:28.134 --> 24:30.267
THAT'S WONDERFUL NEWS.

24:31.404 --> 24:32.803
DO YOU THINK YOU'LL BE
ABLE TO MAKE

24:32.805 --> 24:34.672
SOME SORT OF VACCINE
OUT OF THIS STUFF?

24:34.674 --> 24:36.240
I WISH IT WERE
THAT SIMPLE.

24:36.242 --> 24:38.142
VACCINES ARE VERY
DIFFICULT.

24:38.144 --> 24:40.778
IF THERE WERE A GENE
KNOWN TO BE RESISTANT

24:40.780 --> 24:42.213
OR A SUBJECT
WHO SHOWED IMMUNITY,

24:42.215 --> 24:43.581
WE'D HAVE SOMEWHERE
TO START.

24:43.583 --> 24:44.748
FOR NOW,
WE'RE FLYING BLIND.

24:44.750 --> 24:46.750
WHAT'S ALL THIS STUFF
FOR, THEN?

24:46.752 --> 24:48.686
MY HOPE IS TO SLOW
THE VIRUS DOWN.

24:48.688 --> 24:50.387
IF I CAN FIND
AN EFFECTIVE

24:50.389 --> 24:52.223
ANTIVIRAL AGENT,
MAYBE WE CAN KEEP

24:52.225 --> 24:53.791
PEOPLE ALIVE
LONG ENOUGH TO FIND

24:53.793 --> 24:55.192
A PERMANENT
SOLUTION.

24:55.194 --> 24:57.094
COME BACK BY
IN A FEW HOURS.

24:57.096 --> 24:59.296
YOU CAN SEE HOW IT'S
WORKING.

24:59.298 --> 25:00.931
YEAH. OK.

25:00.933 --> 25:02.600
HEY. I'LL BRING KATIE
WHATEVER SHE NEEDS.

25:02.602 --> 25:04.235
WHICH ONE'S HERS?

25:04.237 --> 25:06.403
THAT'S FINE.
YOU CAN LEAVE IT.

25:06.405 --> 25:08.072
I'LL MAKE TIME.

25:08.074 --> 25:10.941
YOU'VE GOT ENOUGH
ON YOUR PLATE.

25:10.943 --> 25:14.812
I WON'T ASK ANY QUESTIONS,
I PROMISE.

25:14.814 --> 25:16.514
MAN: ALL RIGHT.
THAT'S ABOUT IT.

25:21.554 --> 25:22.786
WELL...

25:22.788 --> 25:25.322
YOU KNOW,

25:25.324 --> 25:27.124
WE CAN MAKE ROOM
FOR ONE MORE

25:27.126 --> 25:30.794
IF WE ALL SQUEEZE
TOGETHER REAL TIGHT.

25:30.796 --> 25:32.863
[MAN LAUGHING]

25:32.865 --> 25:34.031
SHE'S 9 MONTHS'
PREGNANT,

25:34.033 --> 25:35.599
YOU SICK SON
OF A--

25:35.601 --> 25:37.301
[GUNSHOT, LEANNE SCREAMING]

25:37.303 --> 25:39.136
[MAN SPEAKING COMMANDS,
INDISTINCT]

25:42.308 --> 25:44.909
JO-JO, WOULD YOU PLEASE
ASSIST THIS PERVERT

25:44.911 --> 25:46.610
WITH A TOURNIQUET SO HE
STOPS BLEEDING

25:46.612 --> 25:48.445
ON THE FLOOR OF MY SHOP?

25:51.817 --> 25:54.218
GENTLEMEN, IF YOU COULD
KINDLY RETURN

25:54.220 --> 25:55.452
THE MERCHANDISE
TO THE SHELVES

25:55.454 --> 25:57.321
AND REMOVE YOUR VEHICLE
FROM THE PREMISES,

25:57.323 --> 25:58.756
WE MIGHT JUST
GET THROUGH THIS

25:58.758 --> 26:00.157
WITHOUT DROPPING ANY BODIES.

26:00.159 --> 26:02.426
WOULDN'T THAT BE NICE?

26:02.428 --> 26:05.162
LEX: I'D LIKE
TO COMMEND EACH OF YOU

26:05.164 --> 26:07.431
INSIDE THE QUARANTINE
ON YOUR BRAVERY.

26:07.433 --> 26:09.967
I UNDERSTAND HOW
DIFFICULT IT IS

26:09.969 --> 26:11.302
TO ACCEPT CIRCUMSTANCES

26:11.304 --> 26:13.837
WHICH ARE BEYOND
YOUR CONTROL--

26:13.839 --> 26:16.040
TO FEEL HELPLESS.

26:18.477 --> 26:21.946
MANY OF US ARE SEPARATED
FROM OUR LOVED ONES.

26:21.948 --> 26:26.016
WE'RE SCARED.
WE'RE FRUSTRATED.

26:26.018 --> 26:28.185
AND IT TAKES STRENGTH TO BE
ABLE TO SET

26:28.187 --> 26:30.187
THOSE EMOTIONS ASIDE.

26:30.189 --> 26:32.289
BUT IF WE CAN REMAIN CALM--

26:32.291 --> 26:35.359
BUT IF WE CAN REMAIN
CALM

26:35.361 --> 26:38.162
AND DO EXACTLY WHAT IS ASKED
OF US...

26:38.998 --> 26:40.497
BUT IF WE CAN REMAIN CALM

26:40.499 --> 26:43.734
AND DO EXACTLY WHAT IS ASKED
OF US, EVERYTHING WILL BE F--

26:55.881 --> 26:57.047
I CAN'T DO IT.

26:57.049 --> 26:59.116
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING
ABOUT?

26:59.118 --> 27:01.318
"EVERYTHING WILL BE FINE"?

27:01.320 --> 27:03.454
THERE'S PEOPLE DYING
IN THERE LEFT AND RIGHT.

27:03.456 --> 27:06.190
I UNDERSTAND WHY
THE CORDON WENT UP. I DO.

27:06.192 --> 27:07.891
AND I WILL ENFORCE
EVERY RULE

27:07.893 --> 27:09.259
THAT THE SUITS PASS DOWN,

27:09.261 --> 27:10.861
BUT I AM NOT A POLITICIAN.

27:10.863 --> 27:12.529
WHAT DO YOU WANT TO DO?

27:12.531 --> 27:14.298
YOU WANT TO GET UP THERE
AND TELL EVERYONE HOW--

27:14.300 --> 27:15.833
HOW SCARED
THEY SHOULD BE,

27:15.835 --> 27:17.067
HOW WE'RE NOT ANY CLOSER

27:17.069 --> 27:19.203
TO FIGURING
THIS THING OUT?

27:19.205 --> 27:21.171
CHIEF, I BEAN-BAGGED A KID
FOR TRYING TO MAKE

27:21.173 --> 27:22.773
THE BIRTH OF HIS DAUGHTER.

27:22.775 --> 27:24.708
I NEARLY BROKE HIS RIBS.

27:24.710 --> 27:25.909
I'LL LIVE WITH THAT...

27:25.911 --> 27:28.078
BECAUSE I WAS DOING
MY JOB.

27:28.080 --> 27:29.880
BUT WHEN HE WANTED
AN APOLOGY,

27:29.882 --> 27:31.415
I COULDN'T GIVE
HIM ONE.

27:31.417 --> 27:33.450
BECAUSE I WAS
STAYING ON MESSAGE.

27:33.452 --> 27:35.452
THAT AIN'T RIGHT.
IT'S NOT ME.

27:35.454 --> 27:37.755
YOU DO THIS, THERE WILL
BE CONSEQUENCES.

27:37.757 --> 27:39.590
LOMMERS WILL CUT YOU OUT--

27:39.592 --> 27:41.258
NO ACCESS, NO INFORMATION.

27:41.260 --> 27:42.993
YOU SURE THAT'S
WHAT YOU WANT?

27:42.995 --> 27:45.095
THAT'S HER CHOICE
TO MAKE.

27:45.097 --> 27:47.331
THIS IS MINE.

27:54.774 --> 27:56.874
MOM, IT GOES INDIANA,
ILLINOIS.

27:56.876 --> 27:58.575
I'M PRETTY SURE
ILLINOIS IS FIRST.

27:58.577 --> 28:00.044
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

28:00.046 --> 28:02.346
NICE BOARD.

28:02.348 --> 28:03.313
[CHUCKLES]

28:03.315 --> 28:05.115
I GOT THE IDEA FROM
THE MAP YOU MADE.

28:05.117 --> 28:06.450
SMART KID.

28:06.452 --> 28:08.285
[INDISTINCT PA ANNOUNCEMENTS]

28:08.287 --> 28:12.022
HEY. I, UH, I HUNTED
DOWN THAT MEDICATION

28:12.024 --> 28:13.791
YOU WERE ASKING ABOUT.

28:13.793 --> 28:15.959
HOW DID YOU--

28:15.961 --> 28:17.861
DID CANNERTS TELL
YOU ABOUT THAT?

28:17.863 --> 28:19.596
NO. I--I JUST ASKED
IF I COULD HELP.

28:19.598 --> 28:21.131
HE DIDN'T--HE DIDN'T
SAY WHAT IT WAS FOR

28:21.133 --> 28:22.566
OR ANYTHING.

28:22.568 --> 28:24.735
OK.

28:24.737 --> 28:26.136
THANKS.

28:30.076 --> 28:31.975
OH, YOU GOT
YOUR RAILROADS MIXED UP.

28:31.977 --> 28:33.143
IT'S, UH,

28:33.145 --> 28:34.812
IT'S READING,
THEN PENNSYLVANIA,

28:34.814 --> 28:36.313
THEN B&O AND SHORT LINE.

28:36.315 --> 28:38.182
YOU KNOW THE WHOLE
BOARD?

28:38.184 --> 28:41.885
I MEAN, COME ON. WHO
ARE YOU TALKING TO, HUH?

28:41.887 --> 28:44.021
LET ME HELP.

28:44.023 --> 28:45.189
OH, THANK YOU.

28:45.191 --> 28:47.891
[DEVICE BEEPS]

28:47.893 --> 28:50.127
JANA: EASY. SUZY,
NICE AND SLOW.

28:50.129 --> 28:52.296
ONCE WE FIND
A TOWER,

28:52.298 --> 28:53.797
WE HAVE TO KEEP
THE CALLS SHORT.

28:53.799 --> 28:55.432
OUR SIGNAL'S HOT.

28:55.434 --> 28:57.167
ANYONE WATCHING
WILL CATCH IT FAST.

28:57.169 --> 28:59.169
WAIT. STOP.
KEEP IT RIGHT THERE.

28:59.171 --> 29:00.804
DENNIS: WAIT.
WAIT, WAIT. HEY.

29:00.806 --> 29:02.439
I SHOULD GO FIRST.

29:02.441 --> 29:04.074
I--I'M THE ONLY ONE
WITH CHILDREN.

29:04.076 --> 29:05.943
JANA BUILT THE PHONE
TO CALL LEX.

29:05.945 --> 29:07.711
HE'S THE ONLY ONE THAT CAN
TELL US WHAT WE NEED TO KNOW.

29:07.713 --> 29:08.746
WHAT IS LEX GOING
TO DO,

29:08.748 --> 29:10.013
NEGOTIATE
OUR RELEASE?

29:10.015 --> 29:11.215
I MEAN, MY KIDS ARE
PROBABLY OUT THERE--

29:11.217 --> 29:14.151
TERRIFIED.
AND YOU SHOULD BE, TOO.

29:14.153 --> 29:15.886
WE NEED INFORMATION.

29:15.888 --> 29:18.322
JANA GOES FIRST.
END OF DISCUSSION.

29:39.378 --> 29:41.745
WHERE'S THE KID? THE KID.
WHERE'S THE KID?!

29:41.747 --> 29:43.013
I'M SORRY.

29:43.015 --> 29:44.815
LEO GREENE CAME BACK
WITH THESE LAWYERS

29:44.817 --> 29:46.216
AND ALL THESE
LEGAL THREATS.

29:46.218 --> 29:48.485
I NEED AN APB ON
XANDER PAULSON,

29:48.487 --> 29:50.854
AFRICAN AMERICAN MALE,
5'11", 18,

29:50.856 --> 29:52.556
LAST SEEN WITH LEO GREENE.
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

29:52.558 --> 29:54.725
DISPATCHER: COPY THAT.
WILL ISSUE APB

29:54.727 --> 29:55.692
ON ONE XANDER PAULSON,

29:55.694 --> 29:57.661
AFRICAN AMERICAN MALE,
5'11"...

29:57.663 --> 29:59.363
[LEX'S VOICE]
HI. THIS IS LEX.

29:59.365 --> 30:01.598
YOU KNOW WHAT TO DO.

30:08.574 --> 30:10.240
[OVER PA]
FOUR TO SIX FEET AT ALL TIMES.

30:10.242 --> 30:13.076
THESE RULES ARE IN PLACE
FOR YOUR PROTECTION.

30:13.078 --> 30:14.578
MEESE: I HAVE
A BLUE PRIUS REGISTERED

30:14.580 --> 30:16.413
TO LEONARD GREENE
NORTHBOUND

30:16.415 --> 30:19.082
ON RANDOLPH APPROACHING
CORDON PERIMETER.

30:19.084 --> 30:20.417
COPY. EN ROUTE.

30:20.419 --> 30:22.586
WAIT. BUT WE HAVE
A PASSENGER EXITING.

30:22.588 --> 30:24.288
BLACK MALE FLEEING
ON FOOT.

30:24.290 --> 30:25.889
VEHICLE IS TURNING
AROUND.

30:25.891 --> 30:27.257
PLEASE ADVISE.

30:27.259 --> 30:29.193
PURSUE PASSENGER,
NOT VEHICLE.

30:29.195 --> 30:30.894
PURSUE PASSENGER.

30:33.098 --> 30:35.766
[POLICE RADIO TRANSMISSIONS]

30:45.377 --> 30:48.946
ROOF. IT WAS ALL SET UP.

30:48.948 --> 30:50.614
LADDER BRIDGING
TO CONTAINER.

30:50.616 --> 30:53.951
ROPE. IT WAS ALL
WAITING FOR HIM.

30:53.953 --> 30:55.853
SORRY, LEX.

30:55.855 --> 30:57.087
[PANTING]

30:57.089 --> 30:58.989
[MICE SQUEAKING]

31:00.693 --> 31:03.293
THE RAT ON THE RIGHT IS
THE CONTROL RAT.

31:03.295 --> 31:05.295
IT DIDN'T RECEIVE
ANY MEDICATION.

31:05.297 --> 31:06.363
AS YOU CAN SEE,
IT'S ALREADY BEGINNING

31:06.365 --> 31:07.631
TO DETERIORATE.

31:07.633 --> 31:10.200
IT SHOULD START
TO CRASH VERY SOON.

31:10.202 --> 31:11.435
POOR LITTLE GUY.

31:11.437 --> 31:13.804
NOW, IF THE RAT ON
THE LEFT SURVIVES LONGER

31:13.806 --> 31:17.341
THAN THE CONTROL RAT, WE MAY
BE ON TO SOMETHING HERE.

31:21.981 --> 31:23.914
KIND OF EXCITING.

31:27.653 --> 31:28.886
HEY, DOC...

31:28.888 --> 31:30.687
THE RAT ON THE LEFT.

31:44.103 --> 31:45.335
JAKE: WHAT NOW?

31:45.337 --> 31:47.337
WE KEEP TRYING.

31:47.339 --> 31:49.773
THAT'S SCIENCE,
I'M AFRAID...

31:50.743 --> 31:53.010
MORE FAILURES
THAN VICTORIES.

32:07.927 --> 32:10.460
WORKING ON "CHANCE"
OR "COMMUNITY CHEST"?

32:11.730 --> 32:13.530
EITHER.

32:13.532 --> 32:15.132
I CAN'T REMEMBER
ANYTHING

32:15.134 --> 32:17.034
BEYOND "GET OUT
OF JAIL"

32:17.036 --> 32:18.702
AND "BANK ERROR
IN YOUR FAVOR."

32:18.704 --> 32:20.804
WELL, "TAKE A WALK
ON THE BOARDWALK";

32:20.806 --> 32:22.372
"SECOND PRIZE IN
A BEAUTY CONTEST."

32:22.374 --> 32:24.408
HERE. HERE. GIVE ME ONE.

32:27.212 --> 32:28.478
WHERE'S QUENTIN?

32:28.480 --> 32:29.680
HE'S PLAYING WITH
THE REST.

32:29.682 --> 32:31.815
NURSE HELEN'S
LOOKING AFTER THEM.

32:33.385 --> 32:35.385
THIS ONE...

32:35.387 --> 32:38.422
IS ONLY IN THE SPECIAL
QUARANTINE EDITION.

32:44.563 --> 32:47.064
"YOU WIN
A SHOPPING SPREE."

32:50.636 --> 32:52.736
[TELEPHONE LINE CONNECTS]

32:53.973 --> 32:55.772
THIS IS
MAJOR CARNAHAN.

32:55.774 --> 32:56.940
LEX!

32:56.942 --> 32:58.742
JANA?

32:58.744 --> 33:01.678
GOD. I CAN'T BELIEVE
I GOT THROUGH.

33:01.680 --> 33:05.415
IS THIS REALLY YOU?
I MEAN, HOW--HOW--HOW

33:05.417 --> 33:07.417
ARE YOU--HOW ARE YOU
CALLING?

33:07.419 --> 33:10.587
GOD! IT'S SO GOOD
TO HEAR YOUR VOICE.

33:10.589 --> 33:13.023
'CAUSE, LEX, I SAW
YOU ON TV.

33:13.025 --> 33:14.424
YOU WERE
HOLDING BACK.

33:14.426 --> 33:16.760
WHAT'S REALLY GOING
ON OUT THERE, LEX?

33:16.762 --> 33:17.961
[SIGNAL IS LOST]

33:17.963 --> 33:19.629
JANA?

33:20.966 --> 33:23.033
LEX?

33:23.035 --> 33:24.301
[SIGHS]

33:24.303 --> 33:27.070
OH! UH!

33:27.072 --> 33:29.973
JANA? J--JANA?

33:31.810 --> 33:33.377
LEX?

33:37.950 --> 33:39.416
YOU OK, BOSS?

33:39.418 --> 33:40.917
GOT A CALL?

33:40.919 --> 33:45.122
[VOICE OF JANA]
HI. IT'S ME.

33:45.124 --> 33:47.924
I MISS YOU SO MUCH.
I, UH...

33:47.926 --> 33:49.626
GOD. I WISH YOU'D
ANSWER YOUR PHONE.

33:49.628 --> 33:51.395
UM, I'LL TRY YOU
AGAIN

33:51.397 --> 33:52.929
AS SOON AS I CAN.

33:52.931 --> 33:54.464
I HOPE YOU PICK UP.

34:03.409 --> 34:07.077
[VOICE OF JANA]
HI. IT'S ME.

34:07.079 --> 34:10.714
I MISS YOU SO MUCH.
I, UH...

34:10.716 --> 34:12.516
GOD. I WISH YOU'D
ANSWER YOUR PHONE.

34:12.518 --> 34:15.285
UM, I'LL TRY YOU AGAIN

34:15.287 --> 34:16.653
AS SOON AS I CAN.

34:16.655 --> 34:19.022
I HOPE YOU PICK UP.

34:19.024 --> 34:20.857
YOUR GIRL
GOT A PHONE?

34:28.934 --> 34:31.234
THAT KID WAS GOING
IN WITH OR WITHOUT ME.

34:31.236 --> 34:33.503
I JUST MADE IT
SAFER FOR HIM.

34:33.505 --> 34:35.772
IN EXCHANGE
FOR WHAT?

34:35.774 --> 34:38.141
A COUPLE OF FAVORS.
SO WHAT?

34:38.143 --> 34:40.110
GREENE: YOU KNOW,
WE'RE ALL IN THE
SAME BOAT HERE, MAN.

34:40.112 --> 34:41.678
I AM NOT
THE ENEMY.

34:41.680 --> 34:43.580
YOU KNOW
I COULD LOCK YOU UP?

34:43.582 --> 34:46.683
IF HE DIES IN THERE,
THAT'S ON YOU.

34:46.685 --> 34:49.553
OH, HE'S A SMART KID.
HE'S GONNA BE JUST FINE.

34:51.523 --> 34:53.523
I DIDN'T COME HERE TO
PICK A FIGHT WITH YOU.

34:53.525 --> 34:55.592
NO, YOU JUST--YOU JUST
CAME TO CHASE STORIES.

34:55.594 --> 34:56.760
THIS IS NOT
ABOUT STORIES.

34:56.762 --> 34:57.994
THIS IS NOT
ABOUT HEADLINES.

34:57.996 --> 34:59.596
THIS IS ABOUT
WHAT'S HAPPENING

34:59.598 --> 35:00.797
TO THE PEOPLE WE
CARE ABOUT

35:00.799 --> 35:02.766
AND WHO'S
RESPONSIBLE.

35:07.940 --> 35:09.806
IF YOU WANT TO KNOW WHAT
XANDER'S BEEN UP TO,

35:09.808 --> 35:11.908
LOG ON TO THE DRONE
FOOTAGE AT SUNSET.

35:13.812 --> 35:16.012
MAYBE YOU'LL RETHINK
WHICH SIDE OF THIS

35:16.014 --> 35:17.214
YOU WANT TO BE ON.

35:18.517 --> 35:19.983
[JAKE LAUGHING]

35:19.985 --> 35:23.053
WAIT. HA HA! HOW DOES
THIS EVEN GRAB ON?

35:23.055 --> 35:24.721
YES, YES, YES.

35:24.723 --> 35:26.890
THAT IS PURE CLASS
RIGHT THERE.

35:26.892 --> 35:28.892
[LAUGHTER]

35:28.894 --> 35:31.061
OH. THIS IS--
THIS IS VERY MUCH ME.

35:31.063 --> 35:33.663
OOH. HA HA!

35:33.665 --> 35:35.832
NOW YOU HAVE TO TAKE
UP CERAMICS.

35:35.834 --> 35:37.067
[LAUGHS]

35:37.069 --> 35:38.768
YOU KNOW, I ACTUALLY MADE
MY MOM A MUG IN SUMMER CAMP.

35:38.770 --> 35:39.836
YOU DID?

35:39.838 --> 35:40.770
I DID.

35:40.772 --> 35:42.472
I BET SHE STILL
HAS IT.

35:42.474 --> 35:44.241
HA HA. YEAH, SHE WOULD.
SHE, UH,

35:44.243 --> 35:45.942
SHE ACTUALLY--
SHE PASSED AWAY

35:45.944 --> 35:46.810
WHEN I WAS YOUNG.

35:46.812 --> 35:48.378
I'M SORRY TO HEAR THAT.

35:48.380 --> 35:49.546
NO. IT WAS--IT WAS
A LONG TIME AGO.

35:49.548 --> 35:51.248
YOU KNOW, I DON'T KNOW WHY,

35:51.250 --> 35:53.116
BUT I KEPT THE MUG.

35:53.118 --> 35:55.051
IT'S UGLY, IT LEAKS,

35:55.053 --> 35:58.088
AND IT MOCKS ME FROM
THE CUPBOARD WHEN I'M HOME.

36:00.926 --> 36:02.893
THIS COULD BE THE FIRST
TIME I'VE GONE MORE

36:02.895 --> 36:04.494
THAN A DAY WITHOUT
CHECKING MY PHONE.

36:04.496 --> 36:05.762
LIKE, EVER.

36:05.764 --> 36:09.633
YEAH. IT'S KIND OF
NICE, RIGHT?

36:10.969 --> 36:12.602
IT IS.

36:13.605 --> 36:15.138
[IMITATES BRITISH ACCENT]
WELL, HELLO.

36:15.140 --> 36:17.407
[CHUCKLING]

36:17.409 --> 36:19.976
AND THANK YOU.

36:19.978 --> 36:22.679
YOU--YOU TAKE CARE
OF EVERYONE ELSE.

36:22.681 --> 36:24.481
YOU KNOW, YOU DESERVE
A SHOPPING SPREE.

36:24.483 --> 36:27.984
I MEAN FOR THE OTHER
THING--THE PILLS.

36:29.488 --> 36:30.654
I ALWAYS KIND OF HAD
A HARD TIME

36:30.656 --> 36:32.255
WITH MY HIGHS
AND LOWS.

36:32.257 --> 36:34.958
IT GOT PRETTY BAD WHEN I
WAS WITH QUENTIN'S DAD.

36:34.960 --> 36:38.895
WE GOT INTO SOME STUFF
WE SHOULDN'T HAVE.

36:38.897 --> 36:40.997
I GUESS IT MESSED
WITH MY CHEMISTRY.

36:42.267 --> 36:46.269
I WENT CLEAN. HE DIDN'T,
WHICH, OF COURSE,

36:46.271 --> 36:47.871
HIS PARENTS
BLAME ME FOR.

36:47.873 --> 36:52.008
ANYHOW, THE MEDS
KEEP ME IN CHECK.

36:52.010 --> 36:53.777
SO THANK YOU.

36:53.779 --> 36:56.780
HEY, WE'VE ALL GOT
OUR CROSSES.

36:56.782 --> 36:59.983
THAT'S IT? IT DOESN'T
FREAK YOU OUT?

36:59.985 --> 37:01.318
[CHUCKLES]

37:01.320 --> 37:03.253
WHAT, THAT YOU'RE HUMAN?

37:04.556 --> 37:05.555
WHAT?

37:05.557 --> 37:06.590
NOTHING.

37:06.592 --> 37:08.325
[CHUCKLES]

37:08.327 --> 37:09.893
I GUESS I'M TOO USED TO
BEING PUNISHED FOR IT,

37:09.895 --> 37:11.228
YOU KNOW?

37:12.598 --> 37:14.497
WE'RE ALL MESSED UP, KATIE.

37:14.499 --> 37:16.866
ANYONE WHO JUDGES YOU FOR IT

37:16.868 --> 37:19.302
IS JUST--JUST HIDING
THEIR OWN STUFF.

37:20.772 --> 37:23.306
YOUR MOTHER-IN-LAW,
WHAT'S HER NAME?

37:23.308 --> 37:25.342
GRACE.

37:25.344 --> 37:26.343
GRACE.

37:26.345 --> 37:27.744
[KATIE LAUGHING]

37:27.746 --> 37:29.546
I BET YOU GRACE
HAS SOME SKELETONS--

37:29.548 --> 37:31.214
CLOSETS FULL.

37:31.216 --> 37:32.482
[LAUGHING]

37:32.484 --> 37:35.085
OK. YOUR TURN.

37:35.087 --> 37:36.253
MY TURN?

37:36.255 --> 37:38.321
WHAT'S YOUR CROSS?

37:38.323 --> 37:39.356
[LAUGHING]

37:39.358 --> 37:40.290
OH, GOSH.

37:44.029 --> 37:47.264
I DON'T ACTUALLY THINK
GIRLS ARE GROSS.

37:47.266 --> 37:48.665
THAT'S NOT A CROSS.

37:48.667 --> 37:50.267
IT CAN BE.

37:50.269 --> 37:53.103
I'VE, UH, SORT OF
BEEN WITH A LOT OF THEM.

37:53.105 --> 37:54.304
IT'S LIKE, UH,

37:54.306 --> 37:57.774
IT'S LIKE A CRUTCH
OR A--OR A COPING M...

37:57.776 --> 38:00.710
[CHUCKLES]
WHATEVER.

38:00.712 --> 38:02.879
MY CHILDHOOD WASN'T
A PICNIC.

38:02.881 --> 38:05.815
SO I'VE ALWAYS HAD A HARD
TIME LETTING PEOPLE IN.

38:05.817 --> 38:07.550
AS SOON AS I TRY
TO GET CLOSE,

38:07.552 --> 38:09.919
I MOVE ON.

38:09.921 --> 38:11.288
I DON'T KNOW IF THAT'S

38:11.290 --> 38:12.489
A CONFESSION
OR A WARNING.

38:12.491 --> 38:13.990
NO. I--I JUST...

38:13.992 --> 38:16.559
I KNOW WE DON'T KNOW
EACH OTHER ALL THAT WELL

38:16.561 --> 38:18.328
OR--OR ANYTHING.

38:18.330 --> 38:20.563
BUT CIRCUMSTANCES
ARE MAKING IT SO WE'RE

38:20.565 --> 38:23.700
ALL GETTING KIND OF
CLOSE IN HERE.

38:23.702 --> 38:25.835
YOU KNOW? SO...

38:30.742 --> 38:32.776
SO DON'T LET ME RUN, OK?

38:38.216 --> 38:40.016
OK.

38:52.097 --> 38:56.399
SINGER: ♪ NO TIME FOR REST ♪

38:56.401 --> 38:59.703
♪ NO PILLOW FOR MY HEAD ♪

38:59.705 --> 39:02.872
♪ NOWHERE TO RUN FROM THIS ♪

39:02.874 --> 39:06.876
♪ NO WAY TO FORGET ♪

39:06.878 --> 39:10.780
♪ AROUND THE SHADOWS CREEP ♪

39:10.782 --> 39:14.184
♪ LIKE FRIENDS, THEY COVER ME ♪

39:14.186 --> 39:17.620
♪ JUST WANT TO LAY ME DOWN ♪

39:17.622 --> 39:21.157
♪ AND FINALLY TRY
TO GET SOME SLEEP ♪

39:21.159 --> 39:25.028
♪ WE CARRY ON
THROUGH THE STORM ♪

39:25.030 --> 39:28.431
♪ TIRED SOLDIERS IN THIS WAR ♪

39:28.433 --> 39:33.236
♪ REMEMBER
WHAT WE'RE FIGHTING FOR ♪

39:35.140 --> 39:39.075
♪ MEET ME ON THE BATTLEFIELD ♪

39:39.077 --> 39:42.812
♪ EVEN ON THE DARKEST NIGHT ♪

39:42.814 --> 39:45.482
♪ I WILL BE YOUR SWORD
AND SHIELD ♪

